<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pintoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea pintoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only in the suburceolate corolla with exserted stamens. It is perhaps more widely distributed than is suggested here because of confusion with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pintoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea pintoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
